<paragraph blockId="16.[264,1326,284,1350]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,427,843,869]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Variation</emphasis>
. With the usual variations of pile color (white to pale yellow) and tomentum color (yellow to golden yellow). In some females the hair on the ocellar tubercle is brown or black. Males from Texas and some areas of 
<collectingCountry box="[816,906,924,950]" name="Mexico" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Mexico</collectingCountry>
have the gonocoxa flat with only a slight indication of depression or a separating ridge.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
